00:43:59,021 --> 00:44:02,889
I don't care if it was the sainted aunt
of the Apostle Paul.

614
00:44:03,059 --> 00:44:05,220
Well, I just happen to know.

615
00:44:05,394 --> 00:44:07,624
Fella's son of a doctor, paper said.

616
00:44:07,797 --> 00:44:10,994
They're pretty important around here,
you know, a doctor in the country.

617
00:44:11,167 --> 00:44:13,601
They think they're somebody.

618
00:44:13,769 --> 00:44:16,795
And maybe it gets out you're
trying to fix it to get the boy off.

619
00:44:16,973 --> 00:44:18,907
Wouldn't do you any good.

620
00:44:19,308 --> 00:44:22,368
- Now, it appears to me, maybe--
- You don't know a goddamn thing.

621
00:44:23,145 --> 00:44:24,874
Had you been listening...

622
00:44:25,047 --> 00:44:27,675
...I told Jack to prime
the lawyer through a pal.

623
00:44:27,850 --> 00:44:30,614
Find somebody who don't need to
see his name in lights.

624
00:44:30,786 --> 00:44:33,914
That way, nobody knows
who picked him wasn't me.

625
00:44:34,957 --> 00:44:39,223
Might as well been the pope
himself far as anybody knows.

626
00:44:39,795 --> 00:44:41,057
All right.

627
00:44:42,098 --> 00:44:43,725
I get you.

628
00:44:43,899 --> 00:44:45,890
Yeah, just barely.

629
00:45:03,586 --> 00:45:05,486
- Hey, there, Pop.
- How you doing, son?

630
00:45:06,155 --> 00:45:09,682
- How you making out?
- Oh, I'm getting along.

631
00:45:09,859 --> 00:45:12,225
Good to see you.
You looking good.

632
00:45:13,629 --> 00:45:17,429
- I brought the infantry here.
- How are you?

633
00:45:17,600 --> 00:45:20,535
- More prettier than ever.
- Hey, Grandpa.

634
00:45:20,870 --> 00:45:22,462
How you doing, buddy?
How's the arm?

635
00:45:22,638 --> 00:45:25,471
- He gonna be all-American.
- I know he is. I know he is.

636
00:45:27,710 --> 00:45:33,046
All right, governor, sir, here we go.
One, two... .

637
00:45:59,041 --> 00:46:00,565
Bastard.

