864
01:02:29,781 --> 01:02:33,581
<i>Whatever there was to find
in the case of the upright judge...</i>

865
01:02:33,751 --> 01:02:36,549
<i>... would be long-buried
in the past...</i>

866
01:02:36,721 --> 01:02:39,622
<i>... like a dead cat in the back yard.</i>

867
01:02:42,627 --> 01:02:44,492
<i>But what could be buried there
like that...</i>

868
01:02:45,797 --> 01:02:48,493
<i>... in a place like Burden's Landing?</i>

869
01:02:48,866 --> 01:02:51,357
<i>Where you and your friends
grew up...</i>

870
01:02:51,536 --> 01:02:55,302
<i>... shaded
by 300-year-old live oaks...</i>

871
01:02:55,506 --> 01:02:58,066
<i>... and the sense
of your own entitlement.</i>

872
01:02:59,677 --> 01:03:04,307
<i>To dig around that past
in that back yard...</i>

873
01:03:04,549 --> 01:03:10,215
<i>... you must first- - You tell yourself.
- seek out the girl from that past:</i>

874
01:03:10,755 --> 01:03:12,620
<i>Anne Stanton.</i>

875
01:03:12,790 --> 01:03:15,486
<i>The daughter of the governor
back then.</i>

876
01:03:15,827 --> 01:03:18,921
<i>The little sister
of your best friend, Adam...</i>

877
01:03:20,598 --> 01:03:22,327
<i>... who, one day, you noticed...</i>

878
01:03:22,500 --> 01:03:25,435
<i>... and it struck you
kind of all of a sudden...</i>

879
01:03:25,603 --> 01:03:27,969
<i>... wasn't little anymore.</i>

880
01:03:30,808 --> 01:03:34,005
<i>She was the first one
you loved like that.</i>

881
01:03:34,445 --> 01:03:37,278
<i>And the last, it turns out.</i>

882
01:03:39,417 --> 01:03:41,885
<i>So you hold on to her pictures
in your mind...</i>

883
01:03:42,620 --> 01:03:44,451
<i>... year after year...</i>

884
01:03:44,622 --> 01:03:48,752
<i>... in the belief that someday
it'll be like that again...</i>

885
01:03:48,926 --> 01:03:51,360
<i>... even though
you have no evidence.</i>

886
01:03:53,364 --> 01:03:55,229
<i>In church, they call this faith.</i>

887
01:03:57,101 --> 01:03:59,160
<i>So that's what I'll call it.</i>

888
01:03:59,704 --> 01:04:03,231
Every month or so,
I come out here and light a fire.

889
01:04:03,474 --> 01:04:05,465
Dry the place out.

890
01:04:08,045 --> 01:04:10,946
I know it doesn't really
accomplish that...

891
01:04:11,115 --> 01:04:14,642
...but I got a feeling if I didn't,
if nobody ever came...

892
01:04:15,653 --> 01:04:18,121
...the place would just one day
cave in on itself.

893
01:04:18,956 --> 01:04:20,514
