he was still attorney general...

959
01:09:15,052 --> 01:09:17,520
...under Governor Stanton
pulling down 3400 a year...

960
01:09:17,688 --> 01:09:22,352
...while paying off liens on his place
on the Row to the tune of 42,000.

961
01:09:23,828 --> 01:09:26,558
Well, you see there,
you are a detective.

962
01:09:26,731 --> 01:09:28,358
You dug and chinked
the metal box...

963
01:09:28,532 --> 01:09:31,660
...and are enjoying the sound of it
a bit, if I'm not mistaken.

964
01:09:31,836 --> 01:09:33,167
Might still be empty.

965
01:09:33,337 --> 01:09:35,328
No, it's full.

966
01:09:35,506 --> 01:09:38,134
Crawling with maggots
by now, maybe...

967
01:09:38,309 --> 01:09:41,574
...but still a little something they was
chewing on. Just have to look.

968
01:09:41,779 --> 01:09:44,577
Still have to find the key.
And that ain't gonna be easy.

969
01:09:44,782 --> 01:09:47,546
Well, there's nothing easy
that means anything.

970
01:09:47,718 --> 01:09:49,515
You'll do it. I have faith.

971
01:09:51,188 --> 01:09:53,520
I like this one, Slade.

972
01:09:56,060 --> 01:10:01,362
Now, they all is yelling that I got
no right to what's on their table.

973
01:10:01,532 --> 01:10:04,365
What's on their table is theirs.

974
01:10:05,269 --> 01:10:08,238
I'm not trying to take it.

975
01:10:08,405 --> 01:10:11,636
"Go ahead, sit down at that table,"
I tell.

976
01:10:11,976 --> 01:10:15,412
"Have all you want to eat.
Eat till you can't eat no more.

977
01:10:15,579 --> 01:10:19,447
Now, what's left on that table...

978
01:10:19,617 --> 01:10:22,780
...when you can't eat no more,
even if you tried...

979
01:10:22,953 --> 01:10:28,186
...leave that there
because that's for the rest of us."

980
01:10:30,928 --> 01:10:35,092
And for that, they're trying to ruin me.

981
01:10:35,266 --> 01:10:37,791
For taking
what they left on the table...

982
01:10:37,968 --> 01:10:41,460
...and using it
to build something for you!

983
01:10:42,273 --> 01:10:46,403
To build 3000 miles
of paved highways...

984
01:10:46,577 --> 01:10:50,570
...a hundred and eleven new bridges,
208 new schools...

985
01:10:50,748 --> 01:10:54,309
...60,000 brand-new jobs!

986
01:10:59,857 --> 01:11:02,553
Now, they wanna ruin me...

987
01:11:05,462 --> 01:11:07,896
...because they wanna ruin you.

988
01:11:09,567 --> 01:11:14,231
But your will is my strength.

989
01:11:15,139 --> 01:11:18,597
Your need is my justice.

990
01:11:18,776 --> 01:11:23,042
And I won't let them!

991
01:11:35,259 --> 01:11:37,955
It come to me in a dream.

992
01:11:38,329 --> 01:11:41,628
Whilst you were up in Savannah with
your pail and shovel, eating oysters.

993
01:11:41,799 --> 01:11:43,027
What did?

994
01:11:43,667 --> 01:11:47,296
I'm gonna build me
the best-staffed, best-equipped...

995
01:11:47,471 --> 01:11:50,440
...biggest goddamn health center
this state ever saw.

996
01:11:50,608 --> 01:11:54,135
This country ever saw.
The All-Father hisself.

997
01:11:54,311 --> 01:11:58,247
You want me to do what
to further this noble enterprise?

998
01:11:58,415 --> 01:12:00,474
Deliver me my chief of staff.

999
01:12:00,651 --> 01:12:03,449
Fine. You give me a list
of who you're thinking to run it.

1000
01:12:03,621 --> 01:12:05,054
Only one name on it:

1001
01:12:05,556 --> 01:12:07,387
Dr. Adam Stanton.

1002
01:12:07,558 --> 01:12:11,892
That's my boy, Tom! That's the way!
You see that?

1003
01:12:12,096 --> 01:12:16,863
That's an all-American pass.
Goddamn it. Attaboy, Tom!

1004
01:12:22,706 --> 01:12:26,540
Well, somebody gotta
run this hospital.

1005
01:12:26,710 --> 01:12:29,144
He's gotta be the best, don't he?

1006
01:12:29,313 --> 01:12:32,714
- Adam Stanton is not the best.
- Well, he is for what I need.

1007
01:12:32,883 --> 01:12:34,851
They'll never approve
the money otherwise.

1008
01:12:35,586 --> 01:12:37,247
Willie, Adam's an old friend of mine.

1009
01:12:37,421 --> 01:12:39,548
As I certainly know,
else I wouldn't be asking.

1010
01:12:39,723 --> 01:12:41,748
I know him and I know you.
He won't do it.

1011
01:12:42,259 --> 01:12:43,954
What's wrong with me?

1012
01:12:44,128 --> 01:12:46,255
To him, what isn't?

1013
01:12:46,430 --> 01:12:48,398
You're everything
his father fought against.

1014
01:12:48,565 --> 01:12:50,760
He hates what you represent,
if not you yourself.

1015
01:12:51,335 --> 01:12:53,826
I'm not asking him to love me.

1016
01:12:54,004 --> 01:12:56,234
- I'm asking him to run a hospital.
- Your hospital.

1017
01:12:56,407 --> 01:12:59,774
The people's hospital, where any poor
redneck and nigger can get the best...

1018
01:12:59,944 --> 01:13:02,310
...without paying a dime.
He ought to like that.

1019
01:13:02,479 --> 01:13:06,711
No. What you're asking is for him
to put his family's name next to yours.

1020
01:13:06,884 --> 01:13:09,352
So you can trot him out
in front of senators and say:

1021
01:13:09,520 --> 01:13:11,886
"Lookie here,
lookie who I got standing next to me.

1022
01:13:12,056 --> 01:13:15,219
The son of the most honorable man
who ever served this state."

1023
01:13:15,392 --> 01:13:17,121
Just get him.

1024
01:13:24,802 --> 01:13:27,100
Not easy being the son
of a great man.

1025
01:13:29,206 --> 01:13:32,300
It don't look so hard
for my boy Tom out there.

1026
01:13:34,111 --> 01:13:35,908
Far as you know.

1027
01:13:47,157 --> 01:13:48,954
We should go.

1028
01:13:50,160 --> 01:13:53,891
Not yet. Let's go in again.

1029
01:14:09,780 --> 01:14:12,408
<i>The friend of your youth...</i>

1030
01:14:12,950 --> 01:14:15,851
<i>... is the only friend you'll ever have.</i>

1031
01:14:16,020 --> 01:14:18,318
<i>For he doesn't really see you.</i>

1032
01:14:20,324 --> 01:14:24,852
<i>He sees in his mind a face,
which doesn't exist anymore.</i>

1033
01:14:25,029 --> 01:14:26,894
<i>And speaks a name- -</i>

1034
01:14:27,064 --> 01:14:32,798
<i>Spike, Bud, Red, Rusty, Jack.</i>

1035
01:14:33,137 --> 01:14:37,301
<i>- that belongs
to that now nonexistent face.</i>

1036
01:14:38,642 --> 01:14:42,078
<i>He's still the young idealist
you used to be.</i>

1037
01:14:42,379 --> 01:14:45,712
<i>Still sees good and bad
in black and white...</i>

1038
01:14:46,050 --> 01:14:49,178
<i>... and men as sinners or saints,
but never both.</i>

1039
01:14:49,353 --> 01:14:52,379
<i>- Hey, Adam.
- Feels superior in the knowledge....</i>

1040
01:14:52,556 --> 01:14:55,286
<i>... that you no longer
can distinguish the two.</i>

1041
01:14:55,459 --> 01:14:57,654
<i>- Jack.
- That's what drives you to it...</i>

1042
01:14:57,828 --> 01:15:00,262
<i>- ... try to stick the knife in.
- Come on in.</i>

1043
01:15:00,431 --> 01:15:03,832
<i>For there's a kind
of snobbery in failure.</i>

1044
01:15:04,001 --> 01:15:07,061
<i>Like the twist
to the mouth of a drunk.</i>

1045
01:15:09,339 --> 01:15:10,704
You're looking good, Jack.

1046
01:15:10,874 --> 01:15:13,274
Thank you.
I'll take that as a compliment.

1047
01:15:16,814 --> 01:15:18,679
Been playing much?

1048
01:15:19,049 --> 01:15:20,846
Who wants to know, my sister?

1049
01:15:21,318 --> 01:15:23,445
It was just a question.

1050
01:15:24,254 --> 01:15:28,884
- Everything good?
- Yes, Jack, everything's good.

1051
01:15:29,193 --> 01:15:31,559
All right.
I'm gonna tell you something.

1052
01:15:31,728 --> 01:15:35,095
I don't want you to start yelling at me
until I'm finished.

1053
01:15:35,532 --> 01:15:37,397
Governor Stark
wants you as director...

1054
01:15:37,568 --> 01:15:40,230
...of the medical center he's building.
Whatever you want...

1055
01:15:40,804 --> 01:15:43,272
...all you have to do is say,
it's yours.

1056
01:15:43,440 --> 01:15:44,930
- Money?
- I didn't say that.

1057
01:15:45,109 --> 01:15:48,806
What do I want money for?
I got everything I want. Look around.

1058
01:15:48,979 --> 01:15:50,207
I didn't say money.

1059
01:15:50,380 --> 01:15:53,213
Then what?
What's next when that doesn't work?

1060
01:15:53,383 --> 01:15:55,908
- A threat of some kind?
- Of course not.

1061
01:15:56,086 --> 01:15:58,486
That's how he gets things done?
What he relies on?

1062
01:15:58,655 --> 01:16:00,213
The bribe and the threat?

1063
01:16:00,524 --> 01:16:04,460
I would never do that to you
or let anyone else. You know that.

1064
01:16:04,995 --> 01:16:07,293
I don't know what you think
he's thinking, Jack...

1065
01:16:07,464 --> 01:16:10,831
...or what you're thinking,
but couldn't be flattery.

1066
01:16:11,001 --> 01:16:14,061
He's thinking what he thinks about
anybody he wants something from...

1067
01:16:14,238 --> 01:16:16,468
...who doesn't wanna give it.
- Something from their past.

1068
01:16:16,907 --> 01:16:19,933
- You just said he wasn't.
- Not their past, their weakness.

1069
01:16:20,110 --> 01:16:22,203
- Same thing.
- No, it isn't.

1070
01:16:22,379 --> 01:16:25,405
I'm not gonna debate it with you, Jack.
We're not in school anymore.

1071
01:16:25,582 --> 01:16:28,813
I don't care if you know I'm right.
I don't care if I am right. But I am.

1072
01:16:32,823 --> 01:16:35,314
Then what is it, Jack?
What is my weakness?

1073
01:16:36,793 --> 01:16:38,852
You can't look at anybody
with something broke...

1074
01:16:39,029 --> 01:16:40,587
...without wanting to fix it.

1075
01:16:40,764 --> 01:16:43,130
- And that's a weakness?
- Some would say.

1076
01:16:43,300 --> 01:16:44,528
You would say.

1077
01:16:45,569 --> 01:16:47,662
- It's no disgrace.
- Well, then tell me, Jack.

1078
01:16:47,838 --> 01:16:49,863
Tell me, please.
How is that a weakness?

1079
01:16:51,375 --> 01:16:54,139
- I don't need to tell you.
- I think you do.

1080
01:16:54,311 --> 01:16:57,280
If you don't know, I'll leave you
to think about it. It'll come to you.

1081
01:16:57,447 --> 01:17:00,007
No, it won't, Jack.
And you'll have to go to your boss...

1082
01:17:00,184 --> 01:17:02,778
...and tell him you failed
without taking out the big guns.

1083
01:17:02,953 --> 01:17:06,218
So tell me, for your sake,
how is that a weakness?

1084
01:17:06,390 --> 01:17:09,188
Because it makes you do things
you don't wanna do.

1085
01:17:09,359 --> 01:17:11,259
If they're good.

1086
01:17:11,428 --> 01:17:14,158
And this is. He may not be...

1087
01:17:15,199 --> 01:17:16,928
...but this is.

1088
01:17:30,314 --> 01:17:32,339
It was good to see you, Adam.

1089
01:18:04,736 --> 01:18:08,991
Now, before I tell y'all the story
about how this great university...

1090
01:18:09,677 --> 01:18:12,201
...changed the life of a boy
from Mason City...

1091
01:18:12,221 --> 01:18:14,821
...who, by all rights,
should still be swilling hogs...

1092
01:18:15,961 --> 01:18:19,311
...first, I'm gonna set your minds at ease
on another point of interest.

1093
01:18:19,312 --> 01:18:21,719
I brung my checkbook with me.

1094
01:18:27,891 --> 01:18:30,905
- You own one share?
- I do. I just bought it.

1095
01:18:31,278 --> 01:18:33,131
Now, that gives me the right
as a stockholder...

1096
01:18:33,144 --> 01:18:36,366
...to view the company's
equity records, doesn't it?

1097
01:18:45,901 --> 01:18:47,567
Governor, sir?

1098
01:19:44,440 --> 01:19:46,374
Miss Littlepaugh?

1099
01:19:55,751 --> 01:19:57,651
You're from the insurance company.

1100
01:19:58,053 --> 01:20:00,453
No, no, I'm not.

1101
01:20:00,622 --> 01:20:02,920
But I know about your brother's
insurance policy.

1102
01:20:05,027 --> 01:20:07,018
Not that there was much left on it
to collect.

1103
01:20:07,196 --> 01:20:09,994
He borrowed against it
almost down to nothing. Didn't he?

1104
01:20:10,399 --> 01:20:12,458
Which means you lied...

1105
01:20:12,634 --> 01:20:14,431
...for almost nothing.

1106
01:20:14,803 --> 01:20:18,569
Now, don't you go
jumping out a window.

1107
01:20:19,308 --> 01:20:21,003
It wasn't the money...

1108
01:20:21,176 --> 01:20:23,269
...it was the disgrace.

1109
01:20:23,445 --> 01:20:25,879
I wanted him buried in the good part
of the cemetery...

1110
01:20:26,548 --> 01:20:28,948
...not in the back,
with all the sinners.

1111
01:20:29,118 --> 01:20:31,245
Why did he kill himself?

1112
01:20:31,553 --> 01:20:36,513
They drove him to it.
To make room for that thief, Irwin.

1113
01:20:37,526 --> 01:20:39,858
My brother went
to the Justice Department...

1114
01:20:40,028 --> 01:20:42,997
...and told them he knew
all about their man Irwin...

1115
01:20:43,165 --> 01:20:44,655
...and the bribes...

1116
01:20:44,833 --> 01:20:46,164
...but they wouldn't listen.

1117
01:20:49,138 --> 01:20:52,505
- Are you lying to me?
- No, that's what killed him.

1118
01:20:52,908 --> 01:20:55,172
He wrote the letter to me
and told me.

1119
01:20:55,344 --> 01:20:57,710
And then that night he... .

1120
01:20:58,680 --> 01:21:02,878
All right, wait. What letter?

1121
01:21:03,051 --> 01:21:05,451
The letter he wrote me
explaining it all.

1122
01:21:05,621 --> 01:21:09,022
The lawsuit Irwin was paid
to let up on...

1123
01:21:09,191 --> 01:21:11,386
...and how the power company
hid the payoffs...

1124
01:21:11,560 --> 01:21:15,462
...by firing my brother
and giving Irwin his job.

1125
01:21:17,299 --> 01:21:19,267
Where's the letter now?
What happened to it?

1126
01:21:19,434 --> 01:21:20,867
Oh, I have it.

1127
01:21:21,770 --> 01:21:23,203
Kept it all this time?

1128
01:21:25,941 --> 01:21:28,171
You have the letter here?

1129
01:21:33,582 --> 01:21:35,607
<i>You bring down the lion...</i>

1130
01:21:35,784 --> 01:21:37,843
<i>... the rest of the jungle
will quake in fear...</i>

1131
01:21:38,020 --> 01:21:39,885
<i>... and they'll all fall into line.</i>

1132
01:21:41,957 --> 01:21:44,755
Your employer is calling you, Jack.

1133
01:21:51,333 --> 01:21:53,392
Thank you.

1134
01:22:24,967 --> 01:22:26,400
Hello.

1135
01:22:26,668 --> 01:22:28,533
Hello, Anne.

1136
01:22:32,674 --> 01:22:35,643
- What's that?
- Orange soda.

1137
01:22:35,811 --> 01:22:37,073
Two straws.

1138
01:22:38,280 --> 01:22:42,080
- I think I might want something else.
- I didn't say one of them was for you.

1139
01:22:42,818 --> 01:22:45,810
It's the way it's drunk. Tradition.

1140
01:22:49,858 --> 01:22:53,624
- I know you went to see Adam.
- I did. What of it?

1141
01:22:53,795 --> 01:22:55,854
What did you say to him?

1142
01:22:56,031 --> 01:23:00,092
I went there and I offered him a job.
No use blaming me.

1143
01:23:00,269 --> 01:23:02,829
- I'm not blaming you.
- Well, that's what it sounds like.

1144
01:23:03,005 --> 01:23:06,998
That's what you sound like.
If you could hear yourself.

1145
01:23:07,175 --> 01:23:09,268
I want him to take it.
I want you to go back...

1146
01:23:09,444 --> 01:23:11,537
...and ask him again.

1147
01:23:12,281 --> 01:23:16,377
Jack, you know how it is.
My brother is the son of a governor...

1148
01:23:16,551 --> 01:23:19,315
...the grandson of a senator,
the great-grandson of a general.

1149
01:23:19,488 --> 01:23:24,551
<i>She wasn't telling me anything
I didn't already know about Adam.</i>

1150
01:23:25,394 --> 01:23:27,692
<i>But she was doing it
walking next to me...</i>

1151
01:23:27,863 --> 01:23:30,388
<i>... which is all that mattered.</i>

1152
01:23:31,433 --> 01:23:35,665
<i>So I let her go on
as long as she wanted.</i>

1153
01:23:37,739 --> 01:23:41,072
<i>I knew that Adam
had already made his decision.</i>

1154
01:23:41,243 --> 01:23:44,974
<i>He had decided to take the job
when I first brought it up.</i>

1155
01:23:45,681 --> 01:23:49,208
<i>He was just putting some time
between my visit and now...</i>

1156
01:23:49,384 --> 01:23:51,511
<i>... out of pride.</i>

1157
01:23:53,455 --> 01:23:55,980
He needs to do this
to be part of something himself...

1158
01:23:56,158 --> 01:23:57,455
...before he disappears.

1159
01:23:57,626 --> 01:24:01,255
<i>But something about
what she was saying bothered me.</i>

1160
01:24:01,563 --> 01:24:04,088
<i>The way an off-stage noise
bothers you.</i>

1161
01:24:04,266 --> 01:24:05,631
What kind of life is that?

1162
01:24:05,801 --> 01:24:07,428
<i>Something you hear- -</i>

1163
01:24:07,602 --> 01:24:08,830
He's a guardian of dead men.

1164
01:24:09,004 --> 01:24:11,063
<i>- but not clear enough
to catch the meaning of.</i>

1165
01:24:11,239 --> 01:24:14,766
I want him to take it.
He has to do it.

1166
01:24:14,943 --> 01:24:17,343
<i>So you push it aside.</i>

1167
01:24:24,419 --> 01:24:26,979
I guess that's one of your gunmen
I've heard about.

1168
01:24:27,155 --> 01:24:28,383
Sugar Boy, hell, no.

1169
01:24:28,557 --> 01:24:30,752
He just carry that peashooter
for decoration.

1170
01:24:30,926 --> 01:24:34,157
I tell you one thing, though.
Ain't nobody can drive like him.

1171
01:24:38,033 --> 01:24:40,297
So, what do you think, doc?

1172
01:24:41,470 --> 01:24:43,938
I think it'll do the people of the state
some good...

1173
01:24:44,106 --> 01:24:46,404
...and get you some votes.

1174
01:24:46,608 --> 01:24:48,735
There's a lot of ways to get votes.
Cheaper ones.

1175
01:24:50,212 --> 01:24:51,941
So I understand.

1176
01:24:52,114 --> 01:24:54,014
Because there are some things
I understand.

1177
01:24:54,182 --> 01:24:57,276
And some things you don't.
Just like there's some I don't.

1178
01:24:57,452 --> 01:24:59,579
What I do know
is what makes the mare go.

1179
01:24:59,755 --> 01:25:02,087
And that you can always
make goodness out of badness.

1180
01:25:02,257 --> 01:25:05,055
- That would be two things.
- Them's the two things I know, then.

1181
01:25:05,227 --> 01:25:06,455
And both of them wrong.

1182
01:25:06,628 --> 01:25:09,927
No, neither one of them, sir.
I beg your pardon.

1183
01:25:10,098 --> 01:25:12,965
You can always make good from bad,
in all things.

1184
01:25:13,335 --> 01:25:14,734
In politics, poetry...

1185
01:25:14,903 --> 01:25:17,667
...everything in between.
Makes no difference.

1186
01:25:18,140 --> 01:25:20,472
A man writes a sonnet...

1187
01:25:20,642 --> 01:25:22,507
...and it's good.

1188
01:25:22,677 --> 01:25:24,406
Is it less good if it turns out...

1189
01:25:24,579 --> 01:25:27,343
...the dame he wrote it about
is married to someone else?

1190
01:25:27,516 --> 01:25:30,280
That his passion was illicit?

1191
01:25:31,453 --> 01:25:33,683
Come on,
I wanna show you something.

1192
01:25:34,956 --> 01:25:38,221
I wouldn't mind
understanding something, actually.

1193
01:25:39,261 --> 01:25:43,561
Lf, as you say, there's only bad
to start with from conception on...

1194
01:25:43,732 --> 01:25:45,529
...and that good must be made
from bad...

1195
01:25:45,700 --> 01:25:47,691
...then how do you ever know
what the good is?

1196
01:25:48,437 --> 01:25:51,895
Well, that's simple.
You just make it up as you go along.

1197
01:25:52,073 --> 01:25:53,301
Make up what?

1198
01:25:53,475 --> 01:25:55,306
The good. What else
are we talking about?

1199
01:25:55,777 --> 01:25:57,506
Make it up as you go along?

1200
01:25:57,679 --> 01:26:00,147
Yeah. Just like folks have been doing
for a million years.

1201
01:26:00,315 --> 01:26:02,442
Since we fall out of trees,
crawl out the swamp.

1202
01:26:02,617 --> 01:26:04,175
They just cook up what is right.

1203
01:26:04,352 --> 01:26:06,912
If nobody likes that, well,
just cook it up again...

1204
01:26:07,088 --> 01:26:08,749
...a little different with a lid on.

1205
01:26:08,924 --> 01:26:10,152
And you know what?

1206
01:26:10,325 --> 01:26:12,885
Things under a lid
don't look no different than things...

1207
01:26:13,061 --> 01:26:14,892
...not under a lid
when there's one on it.

1208
01:26:15,063 --> 01:26:17,861
You don't have to convince me
of anything, Mr. Stark.

1209
01:26:18,033 --> 01:26:21,196
You've already done that.
I'm here, aren't I?

1210
01:26:21,636 --> 01:26:25,504
That's right.
And you're a good boy too, doc.

1211
01:26:25,674 --> 01:26:27,835
A lot better than you think.

1212
01:26:28,210 --> 01:26:30,337
So goddamn it.

1213
01:26:31,046 --> 01:26:35,073
Don't let none of them bastards
tell you no different.

1214
01:26:45,026 --> 01:26:48,086
I got a question since everybody's
trying to understand everything...

1215
01:26:48,263 --> 01:26:49,958
...all of a sudden.

1216
01:26:51,099 --> 01:26:52,327
Back when we met...

1217
01:26:53,168 --> 01:26:55,159
...at Slade's old place,
when we shook hands--

1218
01:26:55,337 --> 01:26:56,895
Do you remember that moment?

1219
01:26:57,072 --> 01:26:58,596
Like it was yesterday.

1220
01:26:59,808 --> 01:27:02,402
Did you or did you not
give me a wink?

1221
01:27:02,844 --> 01:27:04,869
A wink?

1222
01:27:07,282 --> 01:27:11,048
Well, that's just gonna have to remain
a mystery.

1223
01:27:11,219 --> 01:27:13,779
- You don't remember.
- Sure I do.

1224
01:27:15,090 --> 01:27:16,955
Then...?

1225
01:27:22,464 --> 01:27:24,125
You know, I... .

1226
01:27:24,299 --> 01:27:28,099
I just do recall giving you a wink.

1227
01:27:29,437 --> 01:27:32,235
But then,
maybe I got something in my eye...

1228
01:27:32,407 --> 01:27:34,932
...which would make it more
of a blink.

1229
01:27:36,645 --> 01:27:38,875
Did you have something
in your eye?

1230
01:27:40,215 --> 01:27:42,240
What if I didn't?

1231
01:27:42,851 --> 01:27:44,375
What would that mean?

1232
01:27:44,686 --> 01:27:46,313
That maybe you figured
you and me...

1233
01:27:46,488 --> 01:27:48,979
...had something in common
the others didn't.

1234
01:27:50,592 --> 01:27:55,393
Well, I'm not gonna tell you
and deprive you of the mystery.

1235
01:27:56,164 --> 01:28:00,658
There's just too few honest-to-God
mysteries left to go around.

1236
01:28:04,806 --> 01:28:07,798
And long after I'm dead and gone...

1237
01:28:08,577 --> 01:28:13,537
...and long after these sons of bitches
are dead and gone...

1238
01:28:13,715 --> 01:28:16,946
...I'm talking eternally now...

1239
01:28:18,520 --> 01:28:23,480
...the Willie Stark Hospital
will still be standing.

1240
01:28:23,992 --> 01:28:27,826
Where every man,
woman and child...

1241
01:28:27,996 --> 01:28:31,022
...who's sick or in pain can go in...

1242
01:28:31,199 --> 01:28:33,963
...knowing they'll get
all a man can do.

1243
01:28:34,135 --> 01:28:38,731
Not as charity,
but as a right, as your right!

1244
01:28:38,907 --> 01:28:43,105
As it is that every child
shall have a complete education!

1245
01:28:43,278 --> 01:28:48,614
That no person, aged or infirm,
shall want or beg for bread!

1246
01:28:48,783 --> 01:28:52,617
That no poor man's land
or house will be taxed!

1247
01:28:52,787 --> 01:28:55,984
That you shall not be deprived
of hope!

1248
01:29:02,430 --> 01:29:04,990
And if any man...

1249
01:29:05,834 --> 01:29:08,803
...stands between me...

1250
01:29:09,404 --> 01:29:11,838
...and fulfilling your rights...

1251
01:29:12,007 --> 01:29:15,101
...I will strike him down...

1252
01:29:15,276 --> 01:29:17,870
...so help me God!

1253
01:29:18,046 --> 01:29:22,415
Hip, shin, thigh and neck bone,
I will hit him.

1254
01:29:22,584 --> 01:29:25,052
I will hit him with a meat ax.

1255
01:29:25,220 --> 01:29:27,450
Somebody give me a meat ax...

1256
01:29:27,622 --> 01:29:31,080
...and bring me another one
for my friend and ally!

1257
01:29:31,660 --> 01:29:36,097
Because it's not only God's only son
with us on this one.

1258
01:29:36,264 --> 01:29:40,257
It's the son of the last
great leader of this state:

1259
01:29:40,435 --> 01:29:45,737
Governor Joe Stanton's boy,
Dr. Adam Stanton!

1260
01:30:02,691 --> 01:30:05,956
All right. See there?

1261
01:30:06,127 --> 01:30:09,528
It's not so bad.
It's not gonna kill you.

1262
01:30:29,984 --> 01:30:31,679
What's up?

1263
01:30:32,687 --> 01:30:34,052
Sadie.

1264
01:30:39,894 --> 01:30:41,885
Now he's done it.

1265
01:30:43,565 --> 01:30:46,363
He's done it again,
and I swear this time... .

1266
01:30:46,534 --> 01:30:49,264
- Done?
- Don't act so dumb.

1267
01:30:49,437 --> 01:30:52,634
Or any dumber than you are.
He's two-timing me again.

1268
01:30:52,807 --> 01:30:55,298
Or four or one or whatever timing
you wanna call it...

1269
01:30:55,477 --> 01:30:57,604
...because you're such a smartass.

1270
01:30:57,779 --> 01:31:00,873
- She skate?
- Shut up.

1271
01:31:01,249 --> 01:31:04,582
You and your friends.
Your highbrow friends.

1272
01:31:04,753 --> 01:31:06,948
All the money and privilege
and everything else...

1273
01:31:07,122 --> 01:31:11,320
...you pretend means nothing.
To someone with it, it means nothing.

1274
01:31:13,294 --> 01:31:15,455
Don't look so dumb.
I said it annoys me.

1275
01:31:15,630 --> 01:31:18,098
I have no idea
what you're talking about...

1276
01:31:18,266 --> 01:31:21,360
...or what it was tangled you two up
in the first place, love or hate.

1277
01:31:21,536 --> 01:31:23,003
You know what I'm talking about.

1278
01:31:23,171 --> 01:31:25,366
Maybe you fixed it up.
I'm sure you did.

1279
01:31:25,540 --> 01:31:27,667
Surely he's fixed you up,
like that pathetic...

1280
01:31:27,842 --> 01:31:30,367
...crazy brother of hers,
to say thanks.

1281
01:31:30,545 --> 01:31:35,414
"Thanks, Jack.
She is a looker, I do declare.

1282
01:31:35,583 --> 01:31:38,074
I'm naming you SDP,
yes, sir.

1283
01:31:38,253 --> 01:31:40,949
State Director of Pimps."

1284
01:31:43,825 --> 01:31:45,349
What are you saying?

1285
01:31:49,063 --> 01:31:50,860
Are you saying...?

1286
01:32:01,376 --> 01:32:02,604
Thank you.

1287
01:32:05,713 --> 01:32:07,510
Are you s--?

1288
01:33:16,150 --> 01:33:18,618
<i>I love you.</i>

1289
01:33:36,638 --> 01:33:38,799
We're gonna walk some more.

1290
01:33:43,077 --> 01:33:44,840
All right.

1291
01:33:57,592 --> 01:33:59,287
Hello.

1292
01:33:59,460 --> 01:34:00,859
Hello, Mother.

1293
01:34:01,195 --> 01:34:04,130
Yes, Mother. Yes.

1294
01:34:08,770 --> 01:34:10,465
All right.

1295
01:34:10,905 --> 01:34:12,668
All right, Mother.

1296
01:34:12,840 --> 01:34:14,671
Goodbye.

1297
01:34:21,282 --> 01:34:23,648
She and the Peytons
and the bridge partner...

1298
01:34:23,818 --> 01:34:26,685
...are going to La Grange
for a nightcap.

1299
01:35:02,423 --> 01:35:05,756
- Jackie.
- What?

1300
01:35:07,662 --> 01:35:09,755
I came up here.

1301
01:35:27,949 --> 01:35:31,043
<i>This was years ago,
you understand.</i>

1302
01:35:32,320 --> 01:35:35,778
<i>Back when things
weren't set in concrete.</i>

1303
01:35:37,325 --> 01:35:40,920
<i>Back when you had a way
of changing the course of things.</i>

1304
01:35:41,496 --> 01:35:43,430
<i>If you knew how.</i>

1305
01:35:46,701 --> 01:35:48,828
<i>She was perfect.</i>

1306
01:35:49,971 --> 01:35:52,337
<i>She had always been perfect.</i>

1307
01:35:53,341 --> 01:35:55,832
<i>I wanted to keep her that way...</i>

1308
01:35:56,611 --> 01:35:58,909
<i>... and like this.</i>

1309
01:36:00,314 --> 01:36:03,306
<i>To be young and older...</i>

1310
01:36:03,985 --> 01:36:05,748
<i>... somehow.</i>

1311
01:36:10,725 --> 01:36:14,183
<i>Of course that's not
what it looked like to her.</i>

1312
01:36:17,598 --> 01:36:19,725
<i>When I came home
from school at Christmas...</i>

1313
01:36:19,901 --> 01:36:22,165
<i>... we saw each other, of course.</i>

1314
01:36:22,336 --> 01:36:25,669
<i>We talked about things,
but never that.</i>

1315
01:36:25,840 --> 01:36:28,673
<i>We talked about love in general.</i>

1316
01:36:28,843 --> 01:36:32,609
<i>Like it was the subject of an essay
instead of real.</i>

1317
01:36:33,881 --> 01:36:38,784
<i>She said it was like jumping off
the high dive, love was.</i>

1318
01:36:39,220 --> 01:36:42,155
<i>Or like almost getting drowned.</i>

1319
01:36:42,623 --> 01:36:44,454
<i>Which, honestly,
I didn't understand.</i>

1320
01:36:46,327 --> 01:36:48,420
<i>For a long time.</i>

1321
01:36:52,667 --> 01:36:55,898
<i>You wanna know the reason
I stopped that night?</i>

1322
01:36:56,571 --> 01:36:58,869
<i>It wasn't nobility.</i>

1323
01:36:59,040 --> 01:37:01,508
<i>That's only what I told myself.</i>

1324
01:37:01,909 --> 01:37:04,901
We have all the time
in the world, right?

1325
01:37:12,887 --> 01:37:15,651
<i>It was that I knew something
was about to be taken from us...</i>

1326
01:37:16,724 --> 01:37:21,093
<i>... leaving in its place
something we didn't know.</i>

1327
01:37:22,396 --> 01:37:24,956
<i>Which didn't make her sad...</i>

1328
01:37:25,933 --> 01:37:27,901
<i>... but it did me.</i>

1329
01:37:29,871 --> 01:37:34,274
<i>You only get a couple of moments
that determine your life.</i>

1330
01:37:35,443 --> 01:37:37,741
<i>Sometimes only one.</i>

1331
01:37:39,280 --> 01:37:41,145
<i>And then it's gone.</i>

1332
01:37:44,418 --> 01:37:46,147
<i>Forever.</i>

1333
01:37:49,123 --> 01:37:51,990
I talked to Senator Loden
this morning.

1334
01:37:52,160 --> 01:37:55,061
He said you find something nice
to put on his plate...

1335
01:37:55,229 --> 01:37:58,528
...he might come around.
Vote any way you like.

1336
01:37:58,699 --> 01:38:00,690
While you cut yourself a slice.

1337
01:38:01,469 --> 01:38:03,903
- I ain't saying that.
- I know what you're saying, Tiny.

1338
01:38:04,071 --> 01:38:06,266
You know, I'd rather bust a man
than buy him.

1339
01:38:07,008 --> 01:38:11,672
- Well, that's up to you now.
- Yeah, sure is. Now go on. Get.

1340
01:38:22,890 --> 01:38:26,348
Do you have
any information for me?

1341
01:38:29,063 --> 01:38:31,725
You sure there's not something
you neglected to mention?

1342
01:38:31,899 --> 01:38:33,764
Something you forgot?

1343
01:38:35,803 --> 01:38:37,361
Jack.

1344
01:38:39,373 --> 01:38:40,840
No.

1345
01:38:41,542 --> 01:38:43,032
Nothing.

1346
01:38:45,112 --> 01:38:46,545
Nothing. Well.

1347
01:38:47,582 --> 01:38:51,450
How about that, Sugar? Nothing.
Am I alone in this?

1348
01:38:51,619 --> 01:38:53,519
The bastards
are pounding at the gate...

1349
01:38:53,688 --> 01:38:56,282
...they're gonna put a vote
of impeachment on the calendar!

1350
01:38:56,457 --> 01:38:58,789
They take that vote today, I'm out!

1351
01:39:03,998 --> 01:39:06,865
I need Judge Irwin with me.

1352
01:39:08,069 --> 01:39:10,833
Or at least not against me.

1353
01:39:16,310 --> 01:39:18,904
So whatever it is...

1354
01:39:19,180 --> 01:39:21,273
...that you don't have on him...

1355
01:39:25,753 --> 01:39:27,482
...use it.

1356
01:39:30,958 --> 01:39:33,392
I'm sorry, what did you say?

1357
01:39:33,561 --> 01:39:36,394
I said I'm going over to the judge's.

1358
01:39:37,164 --> 01:39:41,100
Well, you mean later.
He'll be napping this time of day.

1359
01:39:41,269 --> 01:39:43,203
There isn't any time
he'll wanna hear...

1360
01:39:43,371 --> 01:39:44,668
...what I have to tell him.

1361
01:39:46,440 --> 01:39:49,034
He's not well, you know.

1362
01:39:51,112 --> 01:39:53,046
I can't help that.

1363
01:39:54,415 --> 01:39:57,145
I do wish
you wouldn't get mixed up in things.

1364
01:39:58,052 --> 01:40:00,782
It isn't me mixed up in them.

1365
01:40:01,656 --> 01:40:03,521
The judge is napping right now,
Mr. Burden.

1366
01:40:03,691 --> 01:40:06,251
I'll wait in his study
until he comes down.

1367
01:40:17,371 --> 01:40:19,965
Fire this marble.

1368
01:40:21,942 --> 01:40:24,376
Watch the chandelier.

1369
01:40:25,079 --> 01:40:26,546
Okay, you can fire.

1370
01:40:29,250 --> 01:40:32,845
Hello, Jack. I didn't know
you were at your mother's.

1371
01:40:33,020 --> 01:40:34,510
- You just get in?
- Last night.

1372
01:40:35,056 --> 01:40:39,288
Yeah. It's a bit early in the day,
but what do you think?

1373
01:40:39,460 --> 01:40:42,327
A touch of bourbon
never hurt anyone.

1374
01:40:42,496 --> 01:40:43,724
Least not you and me.

1375
01:40:43,964 --> 01:40:47,331
We're indestructible, aren't we,
you and me?

1376
01:40:47,501 --> 01:40:50,163
- No, thanks.
- "No, thanks," he says.

1377
01:40:50,571 --> 01:40:53,301
Begging the question,
as the old man pours just one drink...

1378
01:40:53,474 --> 01:40:55,203
...what's on your mind?

1379
01:40:56,844 --> 01:40:58,573
Out with it.

1380
01:40:59,146 --> 01:41:00,977
You know who I work for.

1381
01:41:01,148 --> 01:41:02,513
How could I forget?

1382
01:41:02,950 --> 01:41:05,976
But let's just sit
and pretend that I have.

1383
01:41:06,220 --> 01:41:07,585
Come sit over here with me.

1384
01:41:19,767 --> 01:41:22,235
The truth is I don't hold
the same low opinion of him...

1385
01:41:22,403 --> 01:41:23,995
...as many of our friends
on the Row.

1386
01:41:24,171 --> 01:41:25,695
I was almost for him at one time.

1387
01:41:25,873 --> 01:41:30,833
He was busting out windowpanes
and, yeah, letting in some fresh air.

1388
01:41:31,011 --> 01:41:35,141
But now I am worried about him
knocking down the whole house.

1389
01:41:35,316 --> 01:41:38,149
So you threw in with his enemies
after you said you wouldn't.

1390
01:41:38,319 --> 01:41:39,843
Oh, Jack.

1391
01:41:40,054 --> 01:41:42,079
What is politics
but a matter of choices?

1392
01:41:42,256 --> 01:41:45,020
You make a choice knowing there's
a chance it's the wrong one.

1393
01:41:45,192 --> 01:41:48,320
You've made a choice
and you know how much it's cost you.

1394
01:41:48,496 --> 01:41:50,794
There's always a price
for everything we do.

1395
01:41:52,199 --> 01:41:54,963
When we came by that night
and were leaving...

1396
01:41:55,136 --> 01:41:56,728
...you said you would think
about it.

1397
01:41:56,904 --> 01:41:59,839
About calling off the dogs?
No, I did not say that.

1398
01:42:00,007 --> 01:42:02,840
Your memory is faulty, sir.
He said, "Think about it"...

1399
01:42:03,010 --> 01:42:04,238
...which I don't have to.

1400
01:42:04,412 --> 01:42:06,676
I don't have to think
about things I already know.

1401
01:42:06,847 --> 01:42:09,441
You should think it over.
Even now...

1402
01:42:09,617 --> 01:42:12,415
...because it's not too late.

1403
01:42:16,290 --> 01:42:18,155
Too late for what?

1404
01:42:22,196 --> 01:42:23,788
Hey, Jack.

1405
01:42:24,598 --> 01:42:26,156
Jesus.

1406
01:42:26,867 --> 01:42:29,335
- What is it?
- Just say you'll back Stark...

1407
01:42:29,503 --> 01:42:31,266
...against these attacks.
- No!

1408
01:42:36,677 --> 01:42:39,510
Now, that has the sound of finality,
don't it?

1409
01:42:39,680 --> 01:42:42,376
- Yes, it does.
- Yeah.

1410
01:43:12,780 --> 01:43:15,715
You know,
I find this difficult to believe.

1411
01:43:15,883 --> 01:43:17,748
For me too.

1412
01:43:18,352 --> 01:43:21,844
And that your boss would even think
he could pressure me.

1413
01:43:22,022 --> 01:43:23,512
Could blackmail me.

1414
01:43:23,757 --> 01:43:28,785
- The first word is better.
- The first word is prettier, not better.

1415
01:43:29,830 --> 01:43:34,426
Don't you know that this stuff
wouldn't stand up? Not in any court.

1416
01:43:34,602 --> 01:43:36,900
It happened almost 25 years ago.

1417
01:43:37,071 --> 01:43:38,561
You couldn't get any testimony...

1418
01:43:39,273 --> 01:43:41,833
...except from that woman
who is related...

1419
01:43:42,009 --> 01:43:45,706
...and whose testimony,
if she gave it...

1420
01:43:45,980 --> 01:43:48,005
...would be worthless.

1421
01:43:49,083 --> 01:43:51,779
And everybody else, Jack...

1422
01:43:53,354 --> 01:43:55,652
...everybody else is dead.

1423
01:43:56,857 --> 01:43:58,552
You're not.

1424
01:43:59,126 --> 01:44:02,095
You're not dead.
And you don't live in any court.

